  <script>/**
 * Evaluate the strength of a user's password.
 *
 * Returns the estimated strength and the relevant output message.
 */
Drupal.evaluatePasswordStrength = function(value) {
  var strength = "high", msg = [], translate = Drupal.settings.password_policy;
  var trimmedSpaces = /^\s+|\s+$/.test(value);
  if (/^\s+$/.test(value)) {
    return { strength: 10, indicatorText: translate.lowStrength, message: translate.allSpaces };
  }
  value = value.replace(/^\s+|\s+$/g,'')
  var i=0;
  var num=0;
  var chr="";
  while(i<value.length) {
    chr=value.charAt(i);
    if(chr.toUpperCase() != chr.toLowerCase()) {
      num++;
    }
    i++;
  }
  if (num<1) {
    strength="low";
    msg.push(translate.constraint_letter);
  }
  if (!value.length || value.length<8) {
    strength="low";
    msg.push(translate.constraint_length);
  }
  var i=0;
  var num=0;
  var chr="";
  while(i<value.length) {
    chr=value.charAt(i);
    if(chr.toUpperCase() != chr.toLowerCase()) {
      if(chr == chr.toUpperCase()) {
        num++;
      }
    }
    i++;
  }
  if (num<1) {
    strength="low";
    msg.push(translate.constraint_uppercase);
  }
  var i=0;
  var num=0;
  var chr="";
  while(i<value.length) {
    chr=value.charAt(i);
    if(chr.toUpperCase() != chr.toLowerCase()) {
      if(chr == chr.toLowerCase()) {
        num++;
      }
    }
    i++;
  }
  if (num<1) {
    strength="low";
    msg.push(translate.constraint_lowercase);
  }
  var i=0;
  var num=0;
  var chr="";
  while(i<value.length) {
    chr=value.charAt(i);
    if("1234567890".indexOf(chr) != -1) {
      num++;
    }
    i++;
  }
  if (num<1) {
    strength="low";
    msg.push(translate.constraint_digit);
  }
  msg = msg.length > 0 ? translate.needsMoreVariation +"<ul><li>"+ msg.join("</li><li>") +"</li></ul>" : "";
  if (trimmedSpaces) {
    msg = msg.concat(translate.trimmedSpaces);
  }
  if (strength == 'high') { level = 100; } else { level = 10; }   if (strength == 'high') { strength = translate.highStrength; }   if (strength == 'medium') { strength = translate.mediumStrength; }   if (strength == 'low') { strength = translate.lowStrength; }   return { strength: level, indicatorText: strength, message: msg };
};

             <!-- Gateway Response Code --> 
             <div class="modal fade" id="gatewayResponseCodes" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true"> 
              <div class="modal-dialog"> 
               <div class="modal-content"> 
                <div class="modal-header"> 
                 <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"><span aria-hidden="true">×</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span> </button> 
                 <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Gateway Response</h4> 
                </div> 
                <div class="modal-body center-block" style="padding: 0;margin: 5%;"> 
                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;"> 
                  <p class="textGreen" style="margin-top: -2%;">Payeezy Gateway Response Codes</p> 
                  <span>Payeezy gateway Response code indicates the status of a transaction as it is sent to the financial institution and returned to the client.</span> 
                  <br> 
                  <i class="textGreen">Ex:</i> The Response Code "00" (Transaction Normal) indicates that the transaction was processed normally. Any response other than "00" indicates that it was not normal. 
                  <br> 
                 </blockquote> 
                 <table class="table table-condensed" style="font-size: 95%;text-align: left;"> 
                  <thead class="well"> 
                   <tr> 
                    <th><span class="textGreen">Code</span> </th> 
                    <th><span class="textGreen">Description</span> </th> 
                   </tr> 
                  </thead> 
                  <tbody> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td colspan="2"><span class="required">This response code indicates that the transaction was processed normally. Please refer to the bank and approval response information for bank approval Status.</span> </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 00 </td> 
                    <td> Transaction Normal </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td colspan="2"><span class="required">The following response codes indicate invalid data in the transaction. In these cases, the data should be changed before attempting to resend the transaction. These response codes are generated by the remote Plug-In.</span> </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 08 </td> 
                    <td> CVV2/CID/CVC2 Data not verified </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 22 </td> 
                    <td> Invalid Credit Card Number </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 25 </td> 
                    <td> Invalid Expiry Date </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 26 </td> 
                    <td> Invalid Amount </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 27 </td> 
                    <td> Invalid Card Holder </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 28 </td> 
                    <td> Invalid Authorization No </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 31 </td> 
                    <td> Invalid Verification String </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 32 </td> 
                    <td> Invalid Transaction Code </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td> 57 </td> 
                    <td> Invalid Reference No </td> 
                   </tr>

                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;"> 
                  <p class="textGreen" style="margin-top: -2%;">Paypal Registration</p> 
                  <span>Before submitting Paypal transactions (ORDER, AUTHORIZE, PURCHASE) to Payeezy, merchant has to obtain Paypal business account and obtain API credentials (user name, password and signature).<br><br><a class="textGreen" href="https://developer.paypal.com/webapps/developer/docs/classic/api/apiCredentials/#navigate-to-the-api-access-page" target="_blank">"Click here"</a> for obtaining the credentials.</span>
                  <br>
                  <hr>
                  <p class="textGreen" style="margin-top: -2%;">Payeezy - E4 Registration</p> 
                  <span>Merchant needs to provide his Paypal API user, password and signature to be registered with his E4 terminal. <span class="textGreen">The image below shows the same.</span></span>

                 <br>
                 <br>
                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;">
                  <p class="textGreen" style="margin-top: -2%;">Paypal Express Checkout API integration</p>

                  <br>
                  <span class="textGreen">Note:</span> 
                  <span>Note: The way Paypal works is that manual approval of transaction has to be done by customer in the Paypal GUI before you could process that transaction with Payeezy. <span class="textGreen">The image below shows the same.</span></span>

             <!-- AVS & CVV2 Response Codes --> 
             <div class="modal fade" id="cvv2AndAVSResponseCodes" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true"> 
              <div class="modal-dialog"> 
               <div class="modal-content"> 
                <div class="modal-header"> 
                 <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"><span aria-hidden="true">×</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span> </button> 
                 <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">AVS &amp; CVV2 Response Codes</h4> 
                </div> 
                <div class="modal-body center-block" style="padding: 0;margin: 5%;"> 
                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;"> 
                  <p class="textGreen" style="margin-top: -2%;">CVV2 Response Code</p> 
                  <span data-original-title="" title=""><br>The following CVV2 response Codes may be generated by First Data to indicate the status of a transaction based on your processing parameters.</span> 
                  <br> 
                 </blockquote> 
                 <table class="table table-condensed" style="font-size: 95%;text-align: left;"> 
                  <thead class="well"> 
                   <tr> 
                    <th>Code</th> 
                    <th>Description</th> 
                   </tr> 
                  </thead> 
                  <tbody> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">M</span> </td> 
                    <td>CVV2/CVC2 Match - Indicates that the card is authentic. Complete the transaction if the <span class="HelpLink">authorization</span> request was approved.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">N</span> </td> 
                    <td>CVV2 / CVC2 No Match – May indicate a problem with the card. Contact the cardholder to verify the CVV2 code before completing the transaction, even if the authorization request was approved.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">P</span> </td> 
                    <td>Not Processed - Indicates that the expiration date was not provided with the request, or that the card does not have a valid CVV2 code. If the expiration date was not included with the request, resubmit the request with the expiration date.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">S</span> </td> 
                    <td>Merchant Has Indicated that CVV2 / CVC2 is not present on card - May indicate a problem with the card. Contact the cardholder to verify the CVV2 code before completing the transaction.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">U</span> </td> 
                    <td>Issuer is not certified and/or has not provided visa <span class="HelpLink">encryption</span> keys</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">I</span> </td> 
                    <td>CVV2 code is invalid or empty</td> 
                   </tr> 
                  </tbody> 
                 </table> 
                 <hr> 
                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;"> 
                  <p class="textGreen" style="margin-top: -2%;">AVS Response Code</p> 
                  <span data-original-title="" title=""><br>The AVS result is a one-character response that indicates the degree of match for the provided address. Currently supported AVS responses are below.</span> 
                  <br> 
                 </blockquote> 
                 <table class="table table-condensed" style="font-size: 95%;text-align: left;"> 
                  <thead class="well"> 
                   <tr> 
                    <th>Code</th> 
                    <th>Description</th> 
                   </tr> 
                  </thead> 
                  <tbody> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td colspan="2"><span class="required">North American Response Codes</span> </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">X</span> </td> 
                    <td> Exact match, 9 digit zip - Street Address, and 9 digit ZIP Code match</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">Y</span> </td> 
                    <td>Exact match, 5 digit zip - Street Address, and 5 digit ZIP Code match</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">A</span> </td> 
                    <td>Partial match - Street Address matches, ZIP Code does not</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">W</span> </td> 
                    <td>Partial match - ZIP Code matches, Street Address does not</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">Z</span> </td> 
                    <td>Partial match - 5 digit ZIP Code match only</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">N</span> </td> 
                    <td>No match - No Address or ZIP Code match</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">U</span> </td> 
                    <td>Unavailable - Address information is unavailable for that account number, or the card issuer does not support</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">G</span> </td> 
                    <td>Service Not supported, non-US Issuer does not participate</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">R</span> </td> 
                    <td>Retry - Issuer system unavailable, retry later</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">E</span> </td> 
                    <td>Not a mail or phone order</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">S</span> </td> 
                    <td>Service not supported</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">Q</span> </td> 
                    <td>Bill to address did not pass edit checks/Card Association can't verify the authentication of an address</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">D</span> </td> 
                    <td>International street address and postal code match</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">B</span> </td> 
                    <td>International street address match, postal code not verified due to incompatable formats</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">C</span> </td> 
                    <td>International street address and postal code not verified due to incompatable formats</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">P</span> </td> 
                    <td>International postal code match, street address not verified due to incompatable format</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">1</span> </td> 
                    <td>Cardholder name matches</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">2</span> </td> 
                    <td>Cardholder name, billing address, and postal code match</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr>

             <!-- Credit Card Payments optional fields modal - AVS Check, Soft Descriptors, Level2 & Level3 --> 
             <div class="modal fade" id="creditCardPaymentOptionalObjectFields" tabindex="-1" role="dialog" aria-labelledby="myModalLabel" aria-hidden="true"> 
              <div class="modal-dialog"> 
               <div class="modal-content"> 
                <div class="modal-header"> 
                 <button type="button" class="close" data-dismiss="modal"><span aria-hidden="true">×</span><span class="sr-only">Close</span> </button> 
                 <h4 class="modal-title" id="myModalLabel">Optional AVS, Soft Descriptors, Level2 &amp; Level3 Properties</h4> 
                </div> 
                <div class="modal-body"> 
                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;"> 
                  <p class="textGreen" style="margin-top: -2%;">Address object for AVS Check</p> 
                  <span>For merchants who have turned on AVS check, would require to provide <span class="textGreen">"billing_address"</span> object in the request payload.</span>
                  <br> 
                  <span>Below is the object format with all the required and optional fields.</span> 
                 </blockquote> 
                 <pre id="alt-json" class="prettyprint" style="overflow: auto; width: 99.5%;">
    "billing_address": {
    "name": "{string}",
    "street": "{string}",
    "city": "{string}",
    "state_province": "{string}",
    "country": "{string}",
    "zip_postal_code": "{string}",
    "email": "{string}",
    "phone": {
    "type": "{string}",
    "number": "{string}"
    }
    }
    </pre> 
                 <br> 
                 <table class="table table-condensed" style="font-size: 85%;text-align: left;"> 
                  <thead class="well"> 
                   <tr> 
                    <th>Property name</th> 
                    <th>Type</th> 
                    <th>Description</th> 
                   </tr> 
                  </thead> 
                  <tbody> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">billing_address</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span></td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">object</span></td> 
                    <td>This optional customer billing address object is used for AVS (Address Verification System) check purpose. </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">street</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span></td> 
                    <td>Standard US address format - "Number, Street Name"</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">city</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span></td> 
                    <td>Nearest city/town/village to the street name provided.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">state_province</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span></td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span></td> 
                    <td>2-letter state code</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">country</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span></td> 
                    <td>2-letter country code.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">zip_postal_code</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span></td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span></td> 
                    <td>5-digit zip code</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">email</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span></td> 
                    <td>customer email address.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">phone</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">object</span></td> 
                    <td>This JSON object holds phone contact details of the customer.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.phone.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">type</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span></td> 
                    <td>Type is required when the PhoneNumber field is populated in a transaction request. Otherwise, it is optional. <br> Only the following values are accepted:<span class="textGreen">H</span> = Home<br> <span class="textGreen">W</span> = Work<br> <span class="textGreen">D</span> = Day<br> <span class="textGreen">N</span> = Night </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">billing_address.phone</span> <br><span class="textGreen">number</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">object</span></td> 
                    <td>Customer phone number field is required is phone object is populated. Phone number length is restricted to <span class="textGreen">14</span> and non digits will be removed before processing. </td> 
                   </tr> 
                  </tbody> 
                 </table> 
                 <br> 
                 <br> 
                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;"> 
                  <p class="textGreen">Soft Descriptors</p> 
                  <span>A descriptor is a piece of identifying information about a merchant, e.g. business name, phone number, city and/or state, which appears on buyers’ credit/debit card statements. These descriptors remind cardholders of the details of the purchase and give them a way to contact the merchant. The standard descriptor information that gets passed through to the cardholder’s statement is the DBA name and customer service phone number that you provide with your merchant account application. </span>
                  <br> 
                  <span>While it is the card issuer’s discretion as to how many characters will show up in each field, if you keep the DBA Name field to fewer than 22 characters and the city field to fewer than 11 characters they should all show up on the cardholder’s statement. Visa requires MOTO merchants to put a phone number in the City field. Ecommerce merchants may use the City field for a URL, email address or phone number. There are additional fields that can be used; however, the majority of those will not appear on a statement. </span>
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <span class="textGreen">Ex:</span>Soft Descriptor: ABCMovies.com Caddyshack 8885551212 
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <span class="textGreen">Note:</span>
                  <br>In this example, ABCMovies.com and Caddyshack are entered in the DBA Name field.
                  <span class="textGreen">Phone numbers should always be entered with numeric characters only.</span> 
                 </blockquote> 
                 <pre id="alt-json" class="prettyprint" style="overflow: auto; width: 99.5%;">
    "soft_descriptors": {
    "dba_name": "{string}",
    "street": "{string}",
    "city": "{string}",
    "region": "{string}",
    "mid": "{string}",
    "mcc": "{string}",
    "postal_code": "{string}",
    "country_code": "{string}",
    "merchant_contact_info": "{string}"
    }
    </pre>

                    <td>JSON object that holds the soft descriptor fields that would be required if this object is populated.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">dba_name</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Business name, required Character Format is ASCII.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">street</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Business address.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">city</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Business city</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">region</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Business region.<br><span class="textGreen">Ex:</span> North East</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">mid</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Merchant ID</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">mcc</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Enter your Merchant Category Code.<br><span class="textGreen">Ex:</span> 8812</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">postal_code</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Business postal/zip code</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">country_code</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>2 digit country code.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">country_code</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>2 digit country code.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">soft_descriptors.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">merchant_contact_info</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td>

                 <br> 
                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;"> 
                  <p class="textGreen">Level II</p> 
                  <span>Level 2 data fields such as Freight, Duty, etc. - values are for informational purposes only and are not directly reflected in the Total Amount field for the transaction when processed. It is up to the Merchant to ensure that the Total Amount of the transaction reflects the desired Level 2 and 3 amounts. <br>The Discount Amount in line items defaults to 0.00 if nothing is entered</span> 
                  <br>
                  <br>
                  <span class="textGreen">Card Types Supported:</span>
                  <br>
                  <ol>
                   <li>Visa</li>
                   <li>Mastercard</li>
                  </ol> 
                 </blockquote> 
                 <pre id="alt-json" class="prettyprint" style="overflow: auto; width: 99.5%;">
    "level2": {
    "tax1_amount": {number},
    "tax1_number": {string},
    "tax2_amount": {number},
    "tax2_number": {string},
    "customer_ref": {string}
    }
    </pre> 
                 <br> 
                 <table class="table table-condensed" style="font-size: 85%;text-align: left;">

                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">level2.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">tax1_amount</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">number</span> </td> 
                    <td>Tax value included in total amount, only applicable to merchants passing level 2 (Corporate Credit Card - Level II) data. <br>For Canadian merchants this field is the PST amount. </td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">level2.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">tax1_number</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Registered number associated with the tax value. Used for reference or government claims purposes and only applicable to merchants passing level 2 (Corporate Credit Card - Level II) data. <br>For Canadian merchants this field is the PST number</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">level2.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">tax2_amount</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">number</span> </td> 
                    <td>Tax value included in total amount, only applicable to merchants passing level 2 (Corporate Credit Card - Level II) data. <br>For Canadian merchants this field is the GST amount.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">level2.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">tax2_number</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Registered number associated with the tax value. Used for reference or government claims purposes and only applicable to merchants passing level 2 (Corporate Credit Card - Level II) data. <br>For Canadian merchants this field is the GST number.</td> 
                   </tr> 
                   <tr> 
                    <td><span class="Object">level2.</span> <br><span class="textGreen">customer_ref</span> <br><span class="required">(optional)</span> </td> 
                    <td><span class="textGreen">string</span> </td> 
                    <td>Merchant defined value that can be used to internally identify the transaction</td>

                 <br> 
                 <blockquote style="font-size: 85%; display: block; line-height: 1.2; color: #999;text-align: justify;">
